    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf the `:messages` window is turned into a split (e.g: `<C-W>L`), running `:messages` again while it is open throws an error:\n\n```\nError in \"msg_history_show\" UI event handler (ns=nvim._ext_ui):\nLua: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua:386: Must specify 'width'\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_win_set_config'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua:386: in function 'win_set_pos'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua:416: in function 'set_pos'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua:374: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui.lua:33: in function 'ui_callback'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui.lua:66: in function </usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_extui.lua:62>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\nlua require(\"vim._extui\").enable {}\nechom \"foo\"\nmessages\nwincmd L\nmessages\n\" Again so the error shows in the window.\n\" (Double SafeState used just so it shows if :sourced after startup, otherwise VimEnter works)\nau SafeState * ++once au SafeState * ++once messages\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0-dev-315+g40351bbbbe\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nN/A\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
